{{Infobox project | name = Defend Innovation | logo = | image = | caption = | mission_statement = How to Fix Our Broken Patent System | commercial = No | type = | products = | location = | country = | owner = | founder = [[Electronic Frontier Foundation]] | primeminister = | key_people = | established = {{Start date|2012|06|19|df=y}} | disestablished = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | funding = | budget = | current_status = | website = {{URL|defendinnovation.org}} }}
'''Defend Innovation''' is a [[patent]] reform project started by [[Electronic Frontier Foundation]] (EFF) in June 2012. The project initially proposed seven changes to United States's patent system, including shortening the term for [[software patent]]s, requirement to provide the running software code along with patent application, and avoidance of liability of an infringer who independently arrives at the patented invention.<ref>{{cite web|title=EFF Launches New Patent Reform Project to Defend Innovation|url=https://www.eff.org/press/releases/eff-launches-new-patent-reform-project-defend-innovation|website=Electronic Frontier Foundation|accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Proposals|url=https://defendinnovation.org/proposals|website=Defend Innovation|accessdate=13 December 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222074452/https://defendinnovation.org/proposals|archivedate=22 December 2015|df=}}</ref>
==Results== Since June 2012, the project collected information about the patent system from lawyers, software engineers, court cases, and other sources. The information collected was combined with EFF's own expertise<ref>{{cite web|title=Patents|url=https://www.eff.org/patent|website=Electronic Frontier Foundation|accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> and compiled in a whitepaper named ''How to Fix Our Broken Patent System'', which details the issues surrounding the patent system and proposes solutions that can be implemented by the Congress, Patent Office, and also the software companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Defend Innovation|url=https://defendinnovation.org/|website=Defend Innovation|accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> The whitepaper is available at the Defend Innovation website.
