This is a '''list of plain English words and phrases''' and the longer, more cumbersome words they can replace. The problem word is listed ''first''; the plain English alternative follows.

[[Plain English]] (or plain language) is communication in English that emphasizes clarity and brevity, and avoids technical language—particularly in official government or business communication. It uses simple, familiar words instead of lengthy, formal words,{{sfn|Schiess|2003-2004|pp=71–75}} avoids [[jargon]], prefers positive words to negative words,{{sfn|SEC|1998|p=27}} and prefers strong verbs to [[Be (verb)#English|''be'' verbs]].{{sfn|Garner|2001}}
