*'''not able''' – unable<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not accept''' – reject<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not certain''' – uncertain<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not unlike''' – similar, alike<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not many''' – few<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not often''' – seldom, rarely<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not the same''' – different<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not...unless''', '''not...except''' – only if<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not...until''' – only when<ref name="auto12"/>
*'''not later than May 10''' – by May 10, before May 11{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: notwithstanding|notwithstanding]]''' – in spite of, still{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''now comes''' – (omit)<ref>{{harvnb|Kimble|2002|p=45}}: "legal jargon"</ref>
*'''null and void''' – use either "null" or "void"{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=129}}<ref name="auto20">{{harvnb|Butt|2006|p=29}}: "jargon"</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Kimble|1998-2000|p=114}}: "redundant doublet"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: numerous|numerous]]''' – many{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2002|p=129}}: "stuffy"</ref><ref name="auto17"/>

==O==
*'''[[wiktionary: objective|objective]]''' – aim, goal{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: obligate|obligate]]''' – bind, compel{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: observe|observe]]''' – see on a _________basis (omit){{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: obtain|obtain]]''' – get<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009b|p=94}}: "officialese"</ref>
*'''off of''' – off{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=130}}
*'''on request''' – if you ask<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''on a daily basis''' – daily
*'''on a X basis''' – Xly (where X is an adjective)
*'''on the basis of''' – by, from<ref name="auto18"/>
*'''on the contrary''' – but, so<ref name="auto19"/>
*'''on the grounds that''' – (omit)<ref name="auto21">{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=594}}: "verbose"</ref>
*'''on the other hand''' – (omit);<ref name="auto21"/> but, so<ref name="auto19"/>
*'''on the part of''' – by{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=131}}<ref name="auto21"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: operate|operate]]''' – run, use, work{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: optimum|optimum]]''' – best, greatest, most{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: option|option]]''' – choice, way{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: orientate|orientate]]''' – orient{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=131}}<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=598}}: "redundant"</ref>
*'''...out''' ('''calculate''', '''cancel,''' '''distribute''', '''segregate''', '''separate''') – omit<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=600}}: "superfluous"</ref>
*'''outside of''' – outside{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=131}}
*'''[[wiktionary: overall|overall]]''' (unless it means the garment)  – (omit)<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=601}}: "vogue word"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: oversight| oversight [v]]]''' – oversee<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=602}}: "jargon"</ref>
*'''owing to the fact that''' – because, since<ref name="auto9"/><ref name="auto10"/>

==P==
*'''[[wiktionary: parameters|parameters]]''' – limits (''except in mathematical and computer-programming uses''){{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2002|p=132}}: "jargonistic vogue word"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: participate|participate]]''' – take part{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''particulars''' – details<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''pass away''' – die<ref name="auto5"/>
*'''per annum''' – a year<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''perchance''' – perhaps<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=618}}: "archaic"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: perform|perform]]''' – do{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: permit|permit]]''' – let{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''pertaining to''' – 	about, of, on{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: perspire|perspire]]''' – sweat<ref name="auto5"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: peruse|peruse]]''' – read<ref name="auto5"/>
*'''PIN number''' – PIN<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=630}}: "redundant"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: place|place]]''' – put<ref name="auto5"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: portion|portion]]''' – part{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: possess|possess]]''' – have, own{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''point in time''', '''particular point in time''' – time, point, now, moment<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=640}}: "clumsy phrase"</ref>
*'''potentiality''' – potential<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=648}}: "jargon"</ref>
*'''[[wiktionary: practicable|practicable]]''' – 	practical{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: preclude|preclude]]''' – prevent{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''preowned''' – used<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2009a|p=653}}: "euphemism"</ref>
*'''preliminary to''', '''[[wiktionary: previous|previous]] to''', '''[[wiktionary: previously|previously]]''', '''prior to''' – before{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=133}}<ref name="auto5"/><ref name="auto9"/><ref name="auto18"/>
*'''preparatory to''' – to prepare for{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=133}}<ref name="auto3"/>
*'''prior to''' – before {{cn|date=October 2017}}
*'''[[wiktionary: prioritize|prioritize]]''' – rank;{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}} set or make priorities{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=134}}
*'''[[wiktionary: proceed|proceed]]''' – do, go ahead, try{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto5"/>
*'''[[wiktionary: procure|procure]]''' – (omit){{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: proficiency|proficiency]]''' – 	skill{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: promulgate|promulgate]]''' – issue, publish{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: provide|provide]]''' – give, offer, say{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''provided that''' – if{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}{{sfn|Garner|2002|p=135}}<ref>{{harvnb|Schiess|2003-2004|pp=57–58}}: "wordy"</ref>
*'''provide guidance for''' – 	guide{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}
*'''[[wiktionary: purchase|purchase]]''' – buy{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}}<ref name="auto5"/><ref name="auto22">{{harvnb|Plain English Campaign|2001|p=11}}: "word to avoid"</ref>
*'''pursuant to''' – by, following, per, under;{{sfn|Simple word suggestions|2013}} in response to, in carrying out, as required by<ref>{{harvnb|Garner|2002|p=136}}: "legalese"</ref><ref name="auto6"/>

